text: Cartersville is an unincorporated community in Florence County, in the U.S. state of South Carolina. ==History== The community was named after the Carter family of early settlers. A post office called Cartersville was established in 1845, and remained in operation until 1953. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in South Carolina Category:Unincorporated communities in Florence County, South Carolina
title: Cartersville, South Carolina
